channel.title: Need help
channel.description: I see that some servers don't use no-ip, or their regular ip address. I saw a deltascape server before that had an ip that said deltascape.org. How can I do this? Also, my router blew out because of the server... do I need a router with higher memory or what? Help please!

item.title: Need help
item.dc:creator: @Insanity6 Insanity6
item.description:
@Insanity6 wrote:

Thanks man… but what about my router… does it need higher memory or bandwith or what? I want to get my server back online. IDK what the problem is… im hosting it off my home router.[quote=“ztr zac, post:2, topic:357282”]No-IP is simply a DNS which is effectively a mask which allows users to connect to an IP address through a name as opposed to a string of numbers. Deltascape.org is exactly the same, just as is moparisthebest.com and google.com. No-ip is a free DNS provider and to get a fully personal DNS it will more than likely cost you money. Just look in google for domain names or DNS providers and you will find alot of information about how to get and use them. :)[/quote]
